<subSubSection id="C32E65595C0CFFA848A6F8B0FB10F808" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8B36D25C0CFFA848A6F8B0FB10F808" blockId="19.[151,1437,1148,2037]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis id="B940EAC05C0CFFA848A6F8B0FEF5F875" bold="true" box="[199,315,1903,1928]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D515C0CFFA84AFEF8AFFCD3F875" baseAuthorityName="Evans" baseAuthorityYear="1959" box="[671,797,1903,1928]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bradleyi">
<emphasis id="B940EAC05C0CFFA84AFEF8AFFCD3F875" box="[671,797,1903,1928]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">A. bradleyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the eye large; the frontal angle of the ocellar triangle acute, and with ocelli large; the pronotal disc with its posterior pronotal sulcus, and the mesotibia not spinose, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D515C0CFFA84900F866FE2EF82C" baseAuthorityName="Evans" baseAuthorityYear="1959" box="[353,480,1976,2001]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bradleyi">
<emphasis id="B940EAC05C0CFFA84900F866FE2EF82C" box="[353,480,1976,2001]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">A. bradleyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the eye small; the frontal angle of the ocellae forming a right angle, and with ocelli very small; the pronotal disc without a posterior pronotal sulcus; and the mesotibia spinose.
</paragraph>
